'''Okitsushima Shrine''' (隠津島神社) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Koriyama, Fukushima|ja|郡山市|12=draft}}, Konan-machi, along {{ill|Fukushima Prefectural Route 235|ja|福島県道235号羽鳥福良線|12=draft}}. It is identified as one of the {{ill|Engishiki|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyocho|12=draft}} shrines in {{ill|Mutsu Province|ja|Mutsu Province|12=draft}}, Asaka District, and recognized as a {{ill|ronsha|ja|論社|12=draft}} (shrine of uncertain status). Its former shrine Ranking was {{ill|Gosha|ja|郷社|12=draft}}. Locally, it is affectionately called "Osugi-sama" or "Osuge-sama."

== Deities ==

The shrine enshrines the following deities:
* {{ill|Ichikishima-hime-no-Mikoto|ja|市杵島比売命|1=Ichikishima-hime|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Tagirihime-no-Mikoto|ja|多岐理毘売命|12=draft}}
* {{ill|Tagitsuhime-no-Mikoto|ja|多岐都比売命|1=Tagitsuhime|12=draft}}

== History ==

According to tradition, the shrine was founded during the {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代|12=draft}} through a {{ill|kanjo|ja|勧請|lt=Enshrinement|1=Kanjō|2=ja|3=分霊|4=es|5=Bunrei|6=id|7=Kanjō|8=zh|9=分靈|10=fr|11=Kanjō|12=draft}} from {{ill|Munakata Taisha|ja|宗像大社|12=draft}} in {{ill|Usa District, Tsukushi Province|ja|筑紫国宇佐郡|12=draft}}. Its sacred grove, spanning approximately 15 hectares, is a dense, primeval forest exuding a mysterious and spiritual ambiance. The area has been designated a {{ill|Natural Monument|ja|天然記念物|12=draft}} of Fukushima Prefecture and selected as one of the {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture's Top 100 Greenery|ja|福島県緑の百景|12=draft}}.

The precincts and nearby areas feature sacred sites such as:
* '''Eboshiiwa''', a sacred rock
* '''Kazaanado''', a subsidiary shrine dedicated to a serpent deity
* '''Suge-no-Taki''', a waterfall historically used for purification rituals ({{ill|misogi|ja|禊|12=draft}})

== Access ==

The shrine is inaccessible during the winter closure of Fukushima Prefectural Route 235, typically from mid-December to mid-April. 

- Approx. 1 hour by car from Koriyama Station.
- No local bus service is available. The nearest bus stop (Aizu Bus) is approximately 7 km away.
