'''Okitsushima Shrine''' (隠津島神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto shrine]] located in [[:en:Kōriyama|Koriyama, Fukushima]], Konan-machi, along {{ill|Fukushima Prefectural Route 235|ja|福島県道235号羽鳥福良線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukushima Prefectural Route 235|qq=|1=Fukushima Prefectural Road Route 235|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11593474}}. It is identified as one of the {{ill|Engishiki|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}} shrines in [[:en:Mutsu Province|Mutsu Province]], Asaka District, and recognized as a {{ill|ronsha|ja|論社|1=candidate shrines|2=ja|3=論社|lt=candidate|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/ronsha|13=User:Immanuelle/candidate shrines|1=Engishiki_Jinmyōchō#Ronsha|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki_Jinmyocho|lt=Ronsha}}}} (shrine of uncertain status). Its former shrine Ranking was {{ill|Gosha|ja|郷社|1=Gō-sha|qid=Q134917316}}{{efn|District Shrines|lt=Ken-sha|1=modern system of ranked Shinto shrines|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gosha|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 近代社格制度|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q712534}}. Locally, it is affectionately called "Osugi-sama" or "Osuge-sama."

== Deities ==

The shrine enshrines the following deities:
* {{ill|Ichikishima-hime-no-Mikoto|ja|市杵島比売命|1=Ichikishima-hime|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichikishima-hime-no-Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Ichikishima-hime|qq=||1=Ichikishima-hime|2=fr|3=Ichikishimahime|4=ja|5=イチキシマヒメ|6=zh|7=市寸島比賣命|8=ru|9=Итикишима-химэ|10=de|11=Ichikishima-hime}}
* {{ill|Tagirihime-no-Mikoto|ja|多岐理毘売命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tagirihime-no-Mikoto|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}
* {{ill|Tagitsuhime-no-Mikoto|ja|多岐都比売命|1=Tagitsuhime|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tagitsuhime-no-Mikoto|13=User:Immanuelle/Tagitsuhime|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to タギツヒメ}}

== History ==

According to tradition, the shrine was founded during the [[:en:Heian period|Heian period]] through a [[:en:Bunrei|Enshrinement]] from [[:en:Munakata Taisha|Munakata Taisha]] in {{ill|Usa District, Tsukushi Province|ja|筑紫国宇佐郡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Usa District, Tsukushi Province|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. Its sacred grove, spanning approximately 15 hectares, is a dense, primeval forest exuding a mysterious and spiritual ambiance. The area has been designated a [[:en:Natural monument|Natural Monument]] of Fukushima Prefecture and selected as one of the {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture's Top 100 Greenery|ja|福島県緑の百景|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fukushima Prefecture's Top 100 Greenery|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.

The precincts and nearby areas feature sacred sites such as:
* '''Eboshiiwa''', a sacred rock
* '''Kazaanado''', a subsidiary shrine dedicated to a serpent deity
* '''Suge-no-Taki''', a waterfall historically used for purification rituals ([[:en:Misogi|misogi]])

== Access ==

The shrine is inaccessible during the winter closure of Fukushima Prefectural Route 235, typically from mid-December to mid-April. 

- Approx. 1 hour by car from Koriyama Station.
- No local bus service is available. The nearest bus stop (Aizu Bus) is approximately 7 km away.
